Turkey Agrees to Train Syrian Opposition on Home Soil to Fight Islamic State
Turkey has agreed to allow the training of at least 2,000 Syrian opposition fighters on Turkish soil by American and Turkish special forces, Turkish officials said on Saturday, as Islamic State militants came closer to capturing the Syrian city of Kobani.
Turkey has long balked at allowing such training on its territory, and officials in both countries said the shift could lend an important boost to the Pentagon-led mission. The training aims to strengthen moderate forces arrayed against Syrian President Bashar al-Assad and...